WEBVTT

00:05.048 --> 00:07.007
[breathing heavily]

00:11.098 --> 00:14.014
[exhales sharply]

00:14.144 --> 00:20.498
[rotary dial clicking]

00:20.629 --> 00:21.630
ALMA: Hello?

00:21.760 --> 00:23.458
Mama.

00:23.588 --> 00:24.850
Have you heard
from Willie Mae?

00:24.981 --> 00:26.330
Willie Mae? No.
Is everything okay?

00:26.461 --> 00:29.768
No. No, it's--
it's not okay.

00:29.899 --> 00:30.813
He's gone.

00:30.943 --> 00:32.641
-Who? Bobo?
-Yes, Bobo.

00:32.771 --> 00:33.685
What do you mean
he's gone?

00:33.816 --> 00:35.122
No, I-I-I don't know.

00:35.470 --> 00:39.474
She said-- she said some men
came and took him last night.

00:39.604 --> 00:40.866
Men? What men?

00:40.997 --> 00:42.607
I don't--
I don't know who.

00:42.738 --> 00:44.522
I-I don't--
I don't know why.

00:44.653 --> 00:47.264
I j-- I just know
that he's gone,

00:47.395 --> 00:50.050
and we have to get someone
down there to go find him.

00:50.180 --> 00:51.181
Take a breath, baby.

00:51.312 --> 00:52.530
I'll call Gene.

00:52.661 --> 00:53.749
You call everyone else.

00:53.879 --> 00:55.098
Okay, I will.

00:55.229 --> 00:56.578
We'll be right over.

00:56.708 --> 00:58.101
Okay.

00:58.232 --> 01:00.103
[receiver clicks]

01:00.234 --> 01:06.283
♪♪

01:06.414 --> 01:12.420
♪♪

01:12.550 --> 01:18.600
♪♪

01:18.730 --> 01:24.780
♪♪

01:24.910 --> 01:31.003
♪♪

01:31.134 --> 01:33.005
UNCLE MOSE: Mnh-mnh.

01:33.136 --> 01:37.749
♪♪

01:37.880 --> 01:42.493
♪♪

01:42.624 --> 01:45.192
-Maurice.
-Yes, sir?

01:45.322 --> 01:47.585
Take the boys
and go into Greenwood.

01:48.804 --> 01:50.458
MAURICE: Why?

01:50.588 --> 01:52.199
Somebody gotta start
looking for him.

01:53.330 --> 01:54.897
Just go on.

01:55.027 --> 01:59.902
♪♪

02:00.032 --> 02:01.643
Crosby...

02:01.773 --> 02:04.254
You'll tell Lizzie...

02:04.385 --> 02:06.082
the boys are going
to stay with family.

02:07.518 --> 02:09.477
You think I'm letting you
go down there alone?

02:13.437 --> 02:14.743
He's my nephew, too.

02:14.873 --> 02:21.619
♪♪

02:21.750 --> 02:22.925
Mama.

02:24.187 --> 02:25.928
I should have never let him
get on that train.

02:27.277 --> 02:28.235
Stop it.

02:28.365 --> 02:29.888
-We're gonna find him.
-How?

02:30.019 --> 02:31.760
He's so far away,
and you really think

02:31.890 --> 02:33.327
the police are gonna
do anything to help us?

02:33.457 --> 02:34.937
Don't you worry, baby.

02:35.067 --> 02:36.765
We don't have to
do this alone.

02:38.158 --> 02:39.159
Were you able
to reach Daddy?

02:39.594 --> 02:40.986
He's coming down from Detroit
as soon as he can,

02:41.117 --> 02:44.076
but he's making calls,
doing his part, even from afar.

02:44.207 --> 02:46.644
We all are.
Hey, Rayfield Mooty.

02:46.775 --> 02:47.732
Mamie's cousin, and I work

02:47.950 --> 02:49.125
at Inland Steel
with her stepfather.

02:49.256 --> 02:50.431
Good to meet you, sir.

02:50.561 --> 02:53.129
Seeing as Rayfield heads
the Steelworkers local,

02:53.260 --> 02:55.479
we thought he might offer
some words of wisdom.

02:55.610 --> 02:58.395
You got yourself a loyal circle,
that's for sure,

02:58.526 --> 03:01.224
but I know some real
powerful folks up here.

03:01.355 --> 03:02.878
Willie Mae.

03:03.008 --> 03:04.967
Tell me everything.

03:05.097 --> 03:07.752
I got the call this morning,
first thing, from Curtis.

03:07.883 --> 03:10.581
He-- he thought what he
heard last night--

03:10.712 --> 03:14.542
those white men taking Bobo--
was all a dream.

03:14.672 --> 03:16.196
But as soon as he realized
that it wasn't,

03:16.326 --> 03:18.023
he ran to the neighbors
and he called.

03:18.154 --> 03:20.591
Did he say why--
why those men came for Bobo?

03:20.722 --> 03:22.985
I-I-I guess there was
some incident before

03:23.115 --> 03:24.465
Curtis got down there.

03:24.595 --> 03:26.206
At some market.

03:26.336 --> 03:27.816
People were saying
Bobo was chatting up

03:27.946 --> 03:30.079
a white woman, being improper.

03:30.210 --> 03:31.254
What?

03:31.385 --> 03:32.342
What did Wheeler say?

03:32.473 --> 03:34.910
Hallie Mae,
have you heard from him?

03:35.040 --> 03:37.042
Not yet.

03:37.173 --> 03:38.783
H-He's on his way home.

03:40.698 --> 03:42.700
Chatting up some white woman?

03:42.831 --> 03:44.354
N-No.

03:44.485 --> 03:46.269
I don't believe one word of it.

03:46.400 --> 03:48.228
I need to hear
from Uncle Mose.

03:48.358 --> 03:51.231
Mama, can you get me that
number of that neighbor of his?

03:51.361 --> 03:54.016
Uh, you know, the one
that got Bobo on the phone.

03:54.059 --> 03:55.452
We've been trying them
all morning.

03:55.583 --> 03:57.106
-No one's answering.
-What about the landlord?

03:57.237 --> 03:58.673
-Whose landlord?
-Uncle Mose's!

03:58.803 --> 03:59.717
Oh. Fr-Frederick.

03:59.848 --> 04:01.241
Uh, Grover Frederick.

04:01.371 --> 04:02.503
Number's in my book.

04:02.633 --> 04:07.682
♪♪

04:07.812 --> 04:12.817
♪♪

04:12.948 --> 04:18.040
♪♪

04:18.170 --> 04:20.608
Hello?
Mr. Frederick?

04:20.738 --> 04:21.739
Hi, this is, um--

04:21.870 --> 04:23.959
this is Mose Wright's niece,
Mamie.

04:24.089 --> 04:27.267
My son, Emmett,
he was down there visiting...

04:27.397 --> 04:30.052
My son. Emmett.

04:30.182 --> 04:32.228
Emmett!

04:32.359 --> 04:34.796
We can't seem to reach anyone
down there, sir, and, um--

04:34.926 --> 04:36.145
and-- and I need to speak
with my Uncle Mose.

04:36.276 --> 04:37.320
It's an emergency.

04:37.625 --> 04:39.583
Can-- can you take down
our number, please?

04:42.456 --> 04:44.371
Or is there someone there
that I can speak to?

04:46.373 --> 04:47.330
Hello?

04:48.331 --> 04:49.898
Hello?

04:50.028 --> 04:55.164
♪♪

04:55.295 --> 04:58.515
Old man says that
there's no one down there,

04:58.646 --> 05:01.823
and he doesn't have a pencil or
paper to take down our number.

05:01.953 --> 05:03.520
Says he's hard of hearing.

05:03.651 --> 05:05.435
He heard me just fine
before I told him

05:05.566 --> 05:07.394
who I was and what I needed.

05:07.524 --> 05:10.310
Folks down there know what it
means when gun-toting white men

05:10.440 --> 05:12.573
storm through a house
in the middle of the night.

05:12.703 --> 05:14.444
They're too afraid
to get involved.

05:14.575 --> 05:15.793
Involved?

05:15.924 --> 05:17.578
My son is hundreds of miles
away from home,

05:17.708 --> 05:19.884
waiting for somebody
to do something.

05:21.669 --> 05:22.713
GENE: Mamie,
what are you thinking?

05:22.844 --> 05:24.498
I'm the one he's waiting for.

05:24.628 --> 05:26.717
I'm catching the first thing
smoking down there.

05:26.848 --> 05:29.416
Those men abducted a child.

05:29.546 --> 05:31.156
I'm sorry, but they sure as hell

05:31.287 --> 05:32.506
ain't gonna be intimidated
by a woman.

05:32.636 --> 05:34.377
I can't think about myself
right now.

05:34.508 --> 05:36.118
Well, what if a call comes in
while you're on the train?

05:36.248 --> 05:39.251
-Mama will handle it.
-What if it's Emmett?

05:41.558 --> 05:44.126
I can't just stay here and wait
for somebody to find it

05:44.256 --> 05:45.693
within their hearts
to pick up their phone

05:45.823 --> 05:47.390
and start looking for him.

05:47.521 --> 05:48.783
RAYFIELD: She's right.

05:49.697 --> 05:52.482
We need more than thoughts
and prayers.

05:52.613 --> 05:53.918
We need to organize.

05:54.049 --> 05:57.748
You need allies up here
with influence.

05:57.879 --> 05:59.576
You need the NAACP.

05:59.707 --> 06:02.362
You really think that
they can help me find him?

06:02.492 --> 06:05.539
I know they'll do a hell of
a lot more than that landlord,

06:05.669 --> 06:07.236
not to mention the law.

06:08.542 --> 06:11.283
My wife and I

06:11.414 --> 06:12.633
heard some talk.

06:12.763 --> 06:13.764
Well, gossip.

06:13.895 --> 06:17.812
That Bobo-- um, Emmett--

06:17.942 --> 06:20.162
Emmett Till--

06:20.292 --> 06:22.512
we heard
that he may have said

06:22.643 --> 06:27.387
or did something
that offended a white lady.

06:27.517 --> 06:30.085
So, you knew what was what
when those men came a-knocking?

06:30.215 --> 06:32.696
Well, sir,
I knew it was trouble.

06:32.827 --> 06:36.047
There had been a lot of talk
coming out of Bryant's market,

06:36.178 --> 06:40.051
so when I asked who was there
and the voice said,

06:40.182 --> 06:41.662
"Mr. Bryant,"

06:41.792 --> 06:44.360
I figured it was about his wife.

06:44.491 --> 06:47.842
I opened the door,
and he stood there, uh,

06:47.972 --> 06:50.801
behind a big guy-- bald--

06:50.932 --> 06:54.588
who said that the lady
was his sister-in-law.

06:54.718 --> 06:58.026
He did most of the talking,
and he had a gun, so I listened.

06:58.156 --> 07:00.550
So they got the boy
and drove off.

07:00.681 --> 07:02.944
Were they alone?

07:03.074 --> 07:07.252
I-It was dark,
but when they first got there,

07:07.383 --> 07:09.603
I think I saw a colored fella.

07:09.733 --> 07:12.606
Uh, I-I couldn't make a face.
He didn't want me to see him.

07:12.736 --> 07:17.698
And when they was leaving,
one of 'em asked

07:17.828 --> 07:20.831
if Emmett was the right one,

07:20.962 --> 07:22.877
and I heard a voice,
a light voice--

07:23.007 --> 07:25.923
lighter than a man's, I mean--
say he was.

07:26.054 --> 07:27.882
Mm-hmm.

07:28.012 --> 07:30.101
Light as in a woman?

07:30.232 --> 07:31.929
Could've been, sir.

07:32.060 --> 07:33.888
But you can't say for sure.

07:34.018 --> 07:36.499
No, sir. I didn't see,
just heard.

07:36.630 --> 07:38.675
Now, you say
you had a house full.

07:38.806 --> 07:41.722
Did anyone else
see all this unfold?

07:41.852 --> 07:43.158
My wife.

07:43.288 --> 07:45.465
She went to stay with family.

07:45.595 --> 07:48.555
My boys are doing the same.

07:48.685 --> 07:51.471
What about the other Chicago
boys you had staying with you?

07:51.601 --> 07:52.863
Where are they?

07:53.168 --> 07:55.344
One's with his uncle, and
the other one headed back north.

07:55.475 --> 07:57.738
Anything else you think
I should know?

08:00.567 --> 08:07.008
Whatever Emmett may have did
or said,

08:07.138 --> 08:10.011
he ain't mean nothing by it.

08:10.141 --> 08:12.187
The boy just turned 14.

08:13.797 --> 08:15.277
That it?

08:18.933 --> 08:20.064
Yes, sir.

08:20.978 --> 08:22.937
All right, then.

08:23.067 --> 08:24.242
I'll fill in the sheriff.

08:26.636 --> 08:29.117
Yes, thank you, sir.

08:29.247 --> 08:35.166
♪♪

08:35.297 --> 08:41.259
♪♪

08:41.390 --> 08:47.265
♪♪

08:47.396 --> 08:49.920
[sighs]

08:50.051 --> 08:52.880
Sheriff, I hate to call you
on your day off,

08:53.010 --> 08:56.057
but, um,
it's them brothers again.

08:57.319 --> 09:00.714
Coming down here is brave
of you, in the midst of it all.

09:00.844 --> 09:03.151
I'd put myself in front
of a bullet

09:03.281 --> 09:05.414
to help find my son,
Mr. Wilkins.

09:05.545 --> 09:07.242
Can you help me,
so I don't have to?

09:07.372 --> 09:09.461
You'd be surprised how quick
people start caring

09:09.592 --> 09:11.159
when the eyes of the nation
are on them.

09:11.289 --> 09:12.943
And how do we do that?

09:13.074 --> 09:15.163
We start local.

09:15.293 --> 09:16.468
"Hometown boy goes missing"

09:16.599 --> 09:18.862
is worthy of a front page,
if you ask me.

09:18.993 --> 09:21.691
So you'll talk to reporters
and get his name out there?

09:21.822 --> 09:23.563
-And his picture?
-Absolutely.

09:23.693 --> 09:25.216
I'm based in New York,

09:25.347 --> 09:28.132
but I will do everything
that I can while I'm here.

09:28.263 --> 09:29.960
In my absence,
I can assure you

09:30.091 --> 09:33.355
that the Chicago branch
of the NAACP will see to it

09:33.485 --> 09:35.923
that the local reporters
will stay on top of it.

09:37.489 --> 09:39.970
[indistinct conversations
in distance]

09:50.459 --> 09:53.897
This isn't my story to tell.

09:54.028 --> 09:56.117
It's yours.

09:56.247 --> 09:59.424
If you let them, people will
take this story, run with it,

09:59.555 --> 10:02.471
and do everything in their power
to profit from it.

10:02.602 --> 10:04.125
That's why I'm here.

10:04.255 --> 10:06.997
I need a professional to help me
navigate all of this.

10:07.128 --> 10:09.957
I could talk to the press
on your behalf.

10:10.087 --> 10:12.568
I do it all the time
when our people are targeted.

10:12.699 --> 10:16.006
But this is not some
voter registration retaliation.

10:16.137 --> 10:19.401
This is a missing child.

10:19.531 --> 10:22.491
And we need to move people
to act.

10:22.622 --> 10:25.233
And if you ask me,
the best person for the job

10:25.363 --> 10:26.669
is the child's mother.

10:26.843 --> 10:30.630
But I wouldn't begin to know
what to say or-- or--

10:30.760 --> 10:32.109
or who to say it to.

10:32.240 --> 10:34.285
Say his name.

10:34.416 --> 10:39.116
Put his face, this face,
in the papers,

10:39.247 --> 10:41.641
and say it to people
who can relate,

10:41.771 --> 10:45.557
people who can see their
children in the face of yours.

10:51.172 --> 10:52.390
[sighs]

10:52.521 --> 10:53.478
What'd you want to go down there

10:53.696 --> 10:55.350
and get that little
nigger boy for?

10:56.525 --> 10:58.658
I don't know,
but I went and got him.

10:58.788 --> 11:00.660
What'd you do with him?

11:00.790 --> 11:02.183
My wife said he wasn't
the right one,

11:02.313 --> 11:03.793
so I turned him loose.

11:05.403 --> 11:07.754
What does that mean?

11:07.884 --> 11:10.191
She said he wasn't the one who
made them ugly remarks to her.

11:11.540 --> 11:12.802
So you brought him here?

11:12.933 --> 11:16.066
-Yeah.
-And what time was that?

11:16.197 --> 11:17.807
Late. Ain't sure.

11:17.938 --> 11:20.375
But it was here
at the market.

11:20.505 --> 11:22.464
She didn't go down
to Preacher's with y'all?

11:22.594 --> 11:28.122
♪♪

11:28.252 --> 11:29.950
[sighs] You really gonna make
a stink out of this, George?

11:30.080 --> 11:32.213
[scoffs]
We just talking, ain't we?

11:33.780 --> 11:35.869
Who went with you
to get him?

11:35.999 --> 11:37.740
Other than your brother.

11:37.871 --> 11:40.264
Nobody.

11:40.395 --> 11:43.050
Where's Mrs. Bryant now?

11:43.180 --> 11:45.705
Family.

11:45.835 --> 11:47.794
So y'all took the boy
and brought him up here

11:47.924 --> 11:52.494
for your wife to identify,
but she said he wasn't the one.

11:52.624 --> 11:54.888
Do I have that right?

11:55.018 --> 11:56.324
Yeah.

11:56.454 --> 11:58.805
Why didn't you take him
back home?

11:58.935 --> 12:00.371
Figured he could
find his own way.

12:00.502 --> 12:02.156
In the middle of the night?

12:05.899 --> 12:07.335
[indistinct conversations]

12:07.465 --> 12:08.815
On behalf of the NAACP,

12:09.032 --> 12:10.991
Mr. Wilkins and his associates
are gonna send telegrams

12:11.121 --> 12:12.383
to officials
all over the country,

12:12.514 --> 12:13.994
demanding that
they get involved.

12:14.124 --> 12:15.952
He even helped me
call the press.

12:16.083 --> 12:17.040
The Black press.

12:17.345 --> 12:19.086
So, I-I guess I gave
anyone who'd listen

12:19.216 --> 12:21.610
an open invitation
to our homes.

12:21.741 --> 12:22.872
Catch your breath.

12:23.003 --> 12:24.265
We may not need all that.

12:25.266 --> 12:26.963
We heard from the Chicago
Police Department.

12:27.094 --> 12:28.965
They've been getting calls
from Mississippi--

12:29.096 --> 12:30.750
three separate reports
from people

12:30.880 --> 12:33.448
who say they saw Emmett.
Alive.

12:33.578 --> 12:34.710
Wait, where did they see him?

12:34.841 --> 12:35.972
Was he hurt?

12:36.233 --> 12:38.322
We don't know much more than
that they saw him,

12:38.453 --> 12:41.935
but according to these tips,
he's on his way home.

12:42.065 --> 12:44.328
What? Mama!

12:44.459 --> 12:46.417
[breathing heavily]

12:48.245 --> 12:49.943
Thank you.

12:50.682 --> 12:54.817
♪♪

12:54.948 --> 12:56.471
Yes, I'm still here.

12:58.647 --> 12:59.822
Are you sure?

12:59.953 --> 13:01.041
It's Emmett.

13:01.171 --> 13:04.392
E-m-m-e...

13:04.522 --> 13:06.350
I don't--
I don't understand.

13:09.832 --> 13:11.312
Oh.

13:11.442 --> 13:16.665
♪♪

13:16.796 --> 13:18.188
What happened?

13:18.319 --> 13:19.973
Mamie?

13:22.018 --> 13:24.412
Well?
What did they say?

13:24.542 --> 13:26.849
The police, they sent me
to the Missing Persons Bureau.

13:26.980 --> 13:29.678
But they had no leads.

13:29.809 --> 13:32.507
All those calls were
nothing more than a hoax.

13:32.637 --> 13:33.725
Every single one of them.

13:33.856 --> 13:34.901
What?

13:35.031 --> 13:37.033
[car doors closing]

13:41.124 --> 13:43.823
Mamie, look.

13:47.000 --> 13:49.263
[indistinct conversations
in distance]

13:49.393 --> 13:52.092
That's the power of the NAACP
for you.

13:52.222 --> 13:54.616
[breathing heavily]

13:54.746 --> 13:56.270
This is our chance.
Come on.

13:56.400 --> 13:58.620
You go.

13:58.750 --> 14:00.927
No one wants to hear
what I'm thinking right now.

14:01.057 --> 14:02.015
MAMIE: Nonsense.

14:02.754 --> 14:05.192
There's no woman who speaks
her mind better than you, Mama.

14:05.322 --> 14:07.368
What's the point, Mamie?

14:07.498 --> 14:09.239
The point?

14:09.370 --> 14:11.067
We keep getting
Emmett's name out there,

14:11.198 --> 14:12.286
and maybe the next phone call

14:12.416 --> 14:14.636
will be the one
that gets him home.

14:14.766 --> 14:16.594
You still believe that?

14:27.605 --> 14:28.868
I'll be right here.

14:34.482 --> 14:36.484
Ma'am, have you-- have you heard
from your family in Mississippi?

14:36.614 --> 14:38.051
Ma'am, do you have any idea of
the identity of the suspect?

14:38.225 --> 14:39.835
Has anyone contacted you
about his possible whereabouts?

14:39.966 --> 14:41.576
Have you been in touch
with the Leflore County Police?

14:41.750 --> 14:43.273
Ma'am, The Greenwood Chronicle
is reporting that three men

14:43.404 --> 14:45.275
and one woman were involved
in your son's disappearance.

14:45.406 --> 14:46.668
Do you know
who these people are?

14:46.798 --> 14:48.496
They're covering it
in the papers down there?

14:48.626 --> 14:49.889
In the afternoon edition, yes.

14:51.629 --> 14:52.979
Thank God.

14:53.109 --> 14:55.024
I'm sorry.
Can we start over?

14:55.155 --> 14:56.765
-Can you repeat your question?
-Sure.

14:56.896 --> 14:59.376
Ma'am, do you-- ma'am, do you
believe your son is still alive?

14:59.507 --> 15:01.422
Yes.

15:01.552 --> 15:04.207
Ma'am, Simeon Booker,
Jetmagazine.

15:04.338 --> 15:06.557
I think I speak
for everyone here when I say

15:06.688 --> 15:07.907
that we're willing
to do our part

15:08.298 --> 15:10.866
to make sure this story
stays in the headlines up here.

15:10.997 --> 15:12.520
We're praying for you.

15:12.650 --> 15:13.869
I appreciate that.

15:14.000 --> 15:15.871
You were kind enough
to invite us here,

15:16.002 --> 15:18.004
so rather than pummel you
with questions,

15:18.134 --> 15:21.268
I think it'd be wise
to let you have the floor.

15:21.398 --> 15:23.400
Tell us about your son.

15:23.531 --> 15:25.620
Start simple.
With his name.

15:30.016 --> 15:33.062
His name is Emmett Till.

15:33.193 --> 15:34.150
He was taken in the middle
of the night

15:34.281 --> 15:35.238
from my uncle's--

15:35.717 --> 15:38.938
um, Mr. Mose Wright's home
in Money, Mississippi.

15:39.851 --> 15:41.418
He was taken by white men.

15:41.549 --> 15:43.594
I think that's important.

15:43.725 --> 15:47.076
And I want people to know
that he is a good boy,

15:47.207 --> 15:50.340
and if anyone can tell us
something to help us find him,

15:50.471 --> 15:54.866
please, I beg you, come forward.

15:54.997 --> 15:56.607
[reporters clamoring]

15:56.738 --> 15:58.740
Sheriff Smith,
have there been any arrests?

15:58.870 --> 15:59.959
When we have something
to report,

16:00.089 --> 16:01.351
you'll be the first to know.

16:01.699 --> 16:04.267
This morning, you were quoted
as saying the missing boy

16:04.398 --> 16:06.356
made some ugly remarks
to a white woman.

16:06.487 --> 16:09.272
Can you elaborate?
What-- what exactly did he say?

16:09.403 --> 16:10.795
I said all I knew then.

16:10.926 --> 16:12.101
I know about the same now.

16:12.232 --> 16:13.929
[clamoring continues]

16:14.060 --> 16:17.193
Y'all making a mountain
out of a molehill.

16:17.324 --> 16:19.717
NAACP really making you work,
ain't they?

16:21.632 --> 16:24.287
I'm not affiliated
with the NAACP.

16:24.418 --> 16:25.549
I'm with the Daily News.

16:25.680 --> 16:27.203
I come up from Jackson.

16:27.334 --> 16:28.770
And I'd like to hear from y'all.

16:28.900 --> 16:30.772
How's this--

16:30.902 --> 16:32.904
Northerners ain't really known
for their manners.

16:33.035 --> 16:34.254
Some of 'em come down here

16:34.384 --> 16:37.039
and learn how things work
the easy way.

16:37.170 --> 16:39.172
Some of 'em don't.

16:45.395 --> 16:46.788
Did I do okay?

16:46.918 --> 16:49.182
Oh, uh, yes, ma'am.

16:49.312 --> 16:51.749
You were great.

16:51.880 --> 16:54.361
Emmett's, uh, 14, right?
Is he in high school?

16:54.491 --> 16:56.580
No. Junior high.

16:58.626 --> 17:01.498
Don't let people forget his age.

17:01.629 --> 17:03.022
It's important.

17:03.152 --> 17:04.153
For next time.

17:04.284 --> 17:05.415
Oh.

17:05.720 --> 17:07.548
I hope I don't have
to do that again. [chuckles]

17:07.678 --> 17:09.202
I hope so, too.

17:09.332 --> 17:14.816
But in the meantime,
I'd like to follow your story

17:14.946 --> 17:16.905
as close as you'll
allow me to get.

17:17.036 --> 17:19.038
As long as you keep Bobo's name
in your papers,

17:19.168 --> 17:21.779
you are welcome
here at Mama's anytime.

17:21.910 --> 17:22.867
My home, as well.

17:22.998 --> 17:24.347
You said Bobo?

17:24.478 --> 17:28.221
Um, it's what we call him,
the people who know him.

17:32.834 --> 17:35.967
[door opens, closes]

17:39.623 --> 17:41.016
Everyone gone?

17:41.147 --> 17:43.584
Nearly. Gene stayed.

17:43.714 --> 17:46.021
He's with Hallie Mae,
trying to soothe her nerves.

17:46.152 --> 17:49.764
She should be thanking God
her boy is on his way home.

17:49.894 --> 17:51.026
If we're gonna
get through this,

17:51.157 --> 17:53.246
I need you to believe
that ours is, too.

17:53.376 --> 17:54.856
You want me to pretend?

17:56.379 --> 17:59.730
I want you to believe.

17:59.861 --> 18:01.080
In him.

18:02.429 --> 18:06.041
He's had people doubting him
since the day he was born.

18:06.172 --> 18:07.869
But we knew better.

18:07.999 --> 18:09.349
We believed in him.

18:09.479 --> 18:11.786
We treated him
like any other boy,

18:11.916 --> 18:14.093
and that belief gave him
confidence...

18:14.223 --> 18:16.660
-[chuckles]
-...and strength,

18:16.791 --> 18:20.011
and an unbelievable will.

18:20.142 --> 18:22.797
If anyone can fight their way
out of something like this,

18:22.927 --> 18:23.928
it's Bobo.

18:24.059 --> 18:26.583
[chuckles] Bobo.

18:27.758 --> 18:29.151
Do you think he'd sit well

18:29.282 --> 18:31.719
knowing you were
doubting his will?

18:31.849 --> 18:36.463
Well, I guess a little hope
never hurt anybody.

18:36.593 --> 18:39.683
Now, that sounds like my mama.

18:39.814 --> 18:41.772
[chuckles]

18:51.652 --> 18:53.132
[door opens]

18:58.093 --> 19:00.922
Wheeler.
Oh, sweet boy, you made it.

19:04.969 --> 19:06.449
[crying]
I'm so sorry, Miss Mamie.

19:06.580 --> 19:08.843
We will talk once
you've settled.

19:08.973 --> 19:11.367
Your mama is missing you
something terrible.

19:11.498 --> 19:12.455
Go on.

19:14.240 --> 19:15.763
Mama.

19:15.893 --> 19:17.939
Wheeler! Oh!

19:18.069 --> 19:20.028
[both crying]

19:22.335 --> 19:24.511
Oh, baby!

19:24.641 --> 19:28.384
♪♪

19:28.515 --> 19:32.301
♪♪

19:32.432 --> 19:34.651
I'm so sorry.

19:34.782 --> 19:36.175
I'm so sorry.

19:36.305 --> 19:42.224
♪♪

19:42.355 --> 19:48.317
♪♪

19:48.448 --> 19:54.367
♪♪

19:54.497 --> 20:00.460
♪♪

20:00.590 --> 20:06.553
♪♪

20:06.683 --> 20:12.646
♪♪

20:12.776 --> 20:14.082
EMMETT: [laughing]
GOBEL: Remember, housewives,

20:14.256 --> 20:16.650
when you go shopping tomorrow,
buy some water.

20:16.780 --> 20:19.740
Water comes in drips, drops,
buckets, barrels, bottles,

20:19.870 --> 20:23.787
and in the giant
economy-sized Lake Michigan.

20:23.918 --> 20:25.485
-EMMETT: [laughs]
-[laughter]

20:25.615 --> 20:27.574
Remember, friends,
without water,

20:27.704 --> 20:30.316
even dial sham won't poo.

20:30.446 --> 20:32.361
-[laughs]
-[laughter]

20:32.492 --> 20:39.281
♪♪

20:39.412 --> 20:46.245
♪♪

20:46.375 --> 20:53.208
♪♪

20:53.339 --> 21:00.171
♪♪

21:00.302 --> 21:07.135
♪♪

21:07.266 --> 21:14.055
♪♪

21:14.185 --> 21:20.975
♪♪

21:21.105 --> 21:22.629
[sighs]

21:25.109 --> 21:26.807
Mamie!

21:28.939 --> 21:29.940
[door closes]

21:30.071 --> 21:31.246
Baby?

21:49.525 --> 21:51.440
Mamie. Baby.

21:51.571 --> 21:53.355
Mm. What?

21:55.357 --> 21:58.142
Oh, I don't know
how I ended up in here.

21:58.273 --> 21:59.840
Wait, how did you...?

22:02.364 --> 22:04.192
Mama gave you her key,
didn't she?

22:05.585 --> 22:07.326
[sighs] That woman.

22:07.456 --> 22:11.025
I think you'll forgive her
when you see this.

22:15.072 --> 22:16.944
[whispering indistinctly]

22:17.074 --> 22:19.599
They filed kidnapping charges.

22:19.729 --> 22:21.165
Bryant admitted
to taking Emmett,

22:21.296 --> 22:22.863
but he said he turned him loose.

22:22.993 --> 22:24.995
Mama, do you hear that?
They let him go.

22:25.126 --> 22:26.562
Our boy is smart.

22:26.736 --> 22:29.348
He's probably hiding in the home
of some nice colored family,

22:29.478 --> 22:30.827
just waiting till
it's safe to phone home.

22:30.958 --> 22:32.046
God willing.

22:32.176 --> 22:33.177
That white woman knows
something.

22:33.308 --> 22:34.614
She's the key.

22:34.744 --> 22:36.833
You believe what they said?

22:36.964 --> 22:38.139
That they can't find her?

22:38.269 --> 22:39.358
They will.

22:39.488 --> 22:41.098
There's a warrant out
for her arrest.

22:41.229 --> 22:42.448
A warrant.

22:42.578 --> 22:43.971
I mean, that--
that's something, isn't it?

22:46.190 --> 22:47.627
It's working.

22:47.757 --> 22:49.368
People are paying attention.

22:55.591 --> 22:58.115
[dog barking in distance]

22:59.639 --> 23:03.294
♪♪

23:03.425 --> 23:06.950
♪♪

23:07.081 --> 23:08.952
[vehicle approaching]

23:09.083 --> 23:13.174
♪♪

23:13.304 --> 23:17.396
♪♪

23:17.526 --> 23:19.441
[brakes squeak]

23:21.791 --> 23:24.838
-[car door opens, closes]
-My boys are in there.

23:24.968 --> 23:27.493
Oh, one of my gals will be happy
to watch over them

23:27.623 --> 23:28.755
while we chat.

23:29.973 --> 23:32.019
Ain't you here to arrest me?

23:32.149 --> 23:33.977
[chuckling] Arrest you?

23:34.108 --> 23:38.068
Now, where would those boys be
with both parents behind bars?

23:38.199 --> 23:40.593
I've been in touch
with the family.

23:40.723 --> 23:42.290
I'm Sidney Carlton, your lawyer.

23:42.421 --> 23:44.771
I don't know what the Milams
are feeding you,

23:44.901 --> 23:46.816
but we ain't got money
for a lawyer.

23:46.947 --> 23:49.123
Oh.
Don't you worry about that.

23:50.080 --> 23:53.910
There's quite a bit
being said about you.

23:54.041 --> 23:56.696
About the incident
at the market.

23:56.826 --> 24:00.656
And I think it's time
we heard your side.

24:00.787 --> 24:05.444
♪♪

24:05.574 --> 24:08.447
A group of Negroes were
on the porch playing checkers.

24:08.577 --> 24:10.013
Was that unusual?

24:10.144 --> 24:11.841
Not at all.
They were locals.

24:11.972 --> 24:13.539
I was familiar.

24:13.669 --> 24:15.062
Go on.

24:15.192 --> 24:19.240
I waited on him,
the Chicago Negro,

24:19.370 --> 24:21.460
and when I went to
take the money, he said,

24:21.590 --> 24:23.113
"How about a date?"

24:23.244 --> 24:25.725
What happened next?

24:25.855 --> 24:27.988
A little nigger from outside
came in to get him,

24:28.118 --> 24:32.166
and when he went out the door,
he said, "Goodbye."

24:32.296 --> 24:33.515
"Goodbye, ma'am"?

24:35.038 --> 24:37.301
How did you handle that?

24:37.432 --> 24:39.956
I got my pistol
from my sister-in-law's car,

24:40.087 --> 24:43.482
and when I came back, the one
from Chicago whistled at me.

24:45.875 --> 24:48.922
Oh, uh, while I went
after the gun,

24:49.052 --> 24:51.228
that's when he whistled.

24:51.359 --> 24:53.796
He didn't do anything further
after he saw the pistol.

24:53.927 --> 24:55.276
Well, thank God for that.

24:57.060 --> 24:58.409
And thank you for coming down.

24:58.540 --> 25:00.237
I know it can be tough,

25:00.368 --> 25:04.067
trying to remember everything,
but don't worry.

25:04.198 --> 25:06.330
In time,
you'll fill in the blanks.

25:06.461 --> 25:07.767
We'll see to it.

25:08.594 --> 25:09.638
Oh, one last thing.

25:09.769 --> 25:11.727
Uh, when you told Roy
about the in--

25:11.858 --> 25:13.163
I didn't want to tell him.

25:13.773 --> 25:14.730
But you did?

25:14.861 --> 25:17.646
He asked.

25:17.777 --> 25:20.519
And he was mighty upset
he had to

25:20.649 --> 25:22.912
hear from someone else first.

25:23.043 --> 25:25.306
Well, was he planning on
confronting the boy?

25:26.612 --> 25:28.614
He didn't say.

25:28.744 --> 25:31.573
Thought he might give him
a whupping or something.

25:31.704 --> 25:33.619
And what do you think
he did with the boy?

25:35.359 --> 25:37.057
He said he let him go.

25:39.407 --> 25:41.888
So, if he were to say
that he brought the boy

25:42.018 --> 25:45.282
to you that same night
so that you could identify him?

25:47.067 --> 25:50.418
I told Roy he wasn't
the right one.

25:50.897 --> 25:53.813
And you have no idea
where he could be now?

25:53.943 --> 25:56.250
No idea at all.

26:00.428 --> 26:05.215
HODGES: ♪ If you see me comin',
better step aside♪

26:05.346 --> 26:08.871
♪ A lotta men didn't,
a lotta men died♪

26:09.002 --> 26:12.614
♪ One fist of iron,
the other of steel♪

26:12.745 --> 26:14.573
♪ If the right one
don't getcha♪

26:14.703 --> 26:16.575
♪ Then the left one will♪

26:17.750 --> 26:20.274
[humming]

26:22.015 --> 26:28.717
♪♪

26:28.848 --> 26:35.550
♪♪

26:35.681 --> 26:42.426
♪♪

26:43.689 --> 26:45.734
[indistinct conversations]

26:49.390 --> 26:55.701
♪♪

26:55.831 --> 27:02.621
♪♪

27:02.751 --> 27:09.540
♪♪

27:09.671 --> 27:11.107
I take it you're family?

27:11.238 --> 27:12.587
Yes, sir.

27:12.718 --> 27:13.893
Go on.

27:14.023 --> 27:15.459
All right,
let him have a look.

27:15.590 --> 27:21.944
♪♪

27:22.075 --> 27:28.472
♪♪

27:28.603 --> 27:30.083
Go ahead.

27:30.213 --> 27:35.262
♪♪

27:35.392 --> 27:40.484
♪♪

27:40.615 --> 27:45.664
♪♪

27:45.794 --> 27:48.362
[indistinct conversations]

27:53.802 --> 27:55.151
Ollie, what's wrong?

27:57.893 --> 27:59.678
What is it?

28:01.331 --> 28:03.638
For God's sakes, whatever it is,
let me have it.

28:05.596 --> 28:07.381
A reporter called.

28:07.511 --> 28:09.731
He didn't want to be
the one to tell you.

28:09.862 --> 28:11.951
They think they found Emmett.
His body.

28:12.081 --> 28:13.300
[woman gasps]

28:13.430 --> 28:18.392
♪♪

28:18.522 --> 28:24.006
♪♪

28:24.137 --> 28:26.008
[Alma crying]

28:26.139 --> 28:32.885
♪♪

28:33.015 --> 28:39.805
♪♪

28:39.935 --> 28:41.458
[pen clicks]

28:41.589 --> 28:42.503
Where did they find him?

28:42.633 --> 28:44.331
The Tallahatchie River.

28:46.072 --> 28:47.595
Do they know what happened?
How did he die?

28:48.509 --> 28:50.903
OLLIE: Nothing official's
come of it yet.

28:51.033 --> 28:52.774
-Where is he now?
-What?

28:52.905 --> 28:54.558
Where is my son?

28:55.908 --> 28:57.083
I suppose he's
with the undertaker.

28:57.213 --> 28:58.388
-Which one?
-I don't know.

28:58.519 --> 28:59.607
Then what good are you?

29:01.348 --> 29:02.828
I need to know
exactly where he is,

29:02.958 --> 29:06.875
and if it really is him,
we gotta bring him home.

29:08.094 --> 29:09.269
Cause of death?

29:09.399 --> 29:10.923
Single bullet to the head.

29:11.053 --> 29:12.751
You need an autopsy
to confirm it?

29:12.881 --> 29:15.318
Well, the water damage
is substantial.

29:15.449 --> 29:17.103
How long did you say
the boy's been missing?

29:17.233 --> 29:18.757
-Three days.
-SMITH: Three days.

29:20.367 --> 29:22.456
Well, I-I've never seen
such damage

29:22.586 --> 29:23.936
in such a short amount of time.

29:24.066 --> 29:26.155
I honestly don't see any use
for an autopsy.

29:26.286 --> 29:28.767
Well, that's it, then.

29:28.897 --> 29:29.768
We'll be taking it from here.

29:29.898 --> 29:30.986
Now, hold on a second.

29:31.117 --> 29:32.771
The boy was abducted
in Leflore County.

29:32.901 --> 29:34.207
That's our jurisdiction.

29:34.424 --> 29:36.992
We ain't talking about
a kidnapping anymore, George.

29:37.036 --> 29:39.212
We found him 10 miles
into Tallahatchie County.

29:39.342 --> 29:40.996
You're on my turf.

29:41.127 --> 29:43.999
I say inquest complete.

29:44.130 --> 29:45.131
Chester...

29:47.089 --> 29:49.135
...you go ahead and release
the body to the family.

29:50.223 --> 29:51.224
Yes, sir.

29:51.833 --> 29:53.922
Suppose I'll set up shipment
to Chicago with Mose Wright?

29:55.489 --> 29:56.925
Chicago?

29:57.056 --> 29:59.928
Ain't no one gonna ship
that body out of Mississippi.

30:00.059 --> 30:02.975
Now, you get it in the ground
immediately,

30:03.105 --> 30:07.066
and you tell ole Mose
it ain't a suggestion.

30:08.067 --> 30:09.546
You hear me, boy?

30:10.896 --> 30:12.332
Yes, sir.

30:16.379 --> 30:18.381
[men grunting]

30:23.082 --> 30:24.823
[automobile approaches]

30:34.441 --> 30:36.704
-[engine shuts off]
-Papa!

30:38.053 --> 30:39.359
I ain't believe it
when I heard.

30:40.534 --> 30:42.057
Now, please tell me
I'm seeing things.

30:42.188 --> 30:44.059
Please tell me you ain't burying
Bo without Mamie's blessing!

30:44.190 --> 30:47.062
Now, we got strict orders from
the law to bury him down here.

30:47.193 --> 30:48.281
To hell with the law!

30:48.411 --> 30:50.631
Quiet yourself.

30:50.761 --> 30:52.241
Already got a target on my back.

30:52.372 --> 30:54.330
What if it were me? Huh?

30:54.461 --> 30:55.505
Or me?

30:55.766 --> 30:57.725
Any one of us could've
turned up in that river.

31:00.162 --> 31:02.077
I don't know
how you do it down here.

31:02.208 --> 31:03.513
How you live.

31:05.211 --> 31:08.344
My whole life is here.

31:08.475 --> 31:09.476
That's how.

31:09.606 --> 31:11.695
Not anymore.

31:11.826 --> 31:13.567
Grandma Lizzie's heading
up north with me.

31:15.177 --> 31:16.396
Hm.

31:18.267 --> 31:19.312
Don't you think Miss Mamie

31:19.486 --> 31:21.053
would want Bobo
on the train with us?

31:21.183 --> 31:25.013
♪♪

31:25.144 --> 31:26.710
[sighs]

31:28.930 --> 31:30.845
WILKINS: It would appear
from this lynching

31:30.976 --> 31:32.891
that the state of Mississippi
has decided

31:33.021 --> 31:37.112
to maintain white supremacy
by murdering children.

31:37.243 --> 31:40.028
The killers of the boy
felt free to lynch him

31:40.159 --> 31:42.639
because there is,
in the entire state,

31:42.770 --> 31:44.903
no restraining influence
of decency.

31:45.033 --> 31:46.121
-That's his chair.
-GENE: What?

31:46.295 --> 31:47.644
We have protested
to Governor White,

31:47.775 --> 31:49.516
seeking his help via telegram,

31:49.646 --> 31:53.259
but judging by past actions
of the state chief executive...

31:53.389 --> 31:54.347
Uh, I didn't even think...

31:54.477 --> 31:56.871
...little action
can be expected.

31:57.002 --> 31:58.481
It's new.

31:58.612 --> 32:00.396
He barely used it.

32:00.527 --> 32:03.051
MAN: Wherever there is
any kind of...

32:03.182 --> 32:05.488
♪♪

32:05.619 --> 32:07.142
GENE: You can cry.

32:10.058 --> 32:11.668
You know that, right?

32:15.281 --> 32:16.978
There's no prize
for holding it in.

32:18.675 --> 32:22.592
There'll be plenty of time
for me to cry when he's home.

32:23.376 --> 32:25.334
[telephone rings]

32:29.034 --> 32:30.731
Hello?

32:30.861 --> 32:32.428
Uncle Crosby.

32:32.559 --> 32:33.647
Thank God.

32:33.777 --> 32:35.475
How's Uncle Mose holding up?

32:37.912 --> 32:39.305
What now?

32:41.394 --> 32:43.091
No.

32:43.222 --> 32:44.527
No, no.

32:44.658 --> 32:47.095
D-Don't you tell me that.

32:47.226 --> 32:48.967
Don't you dare tell me that!

32:49.097 --> 32:50.403
[receiver slams]

32:51.839 --> 32:53.797
They're trying to cover it up.

32:55.103 --> 32:58.106
RAYNER: The whole city is
praying for you and your boy.

32:58.237 --> 33:00.065
Meanwhile, in Mississippi,
they're trying to shove him

33:00.195 --> 33:01.762
in the ground
like he never existed.

33:02.937 --> 33:06.462
I want him to rest
where he was loved,

33:06.593 --> 33:09.857
where he had the right
to look a person in the eye.

33:09.988 --> 33:12.468
RAYNER: I have contacts
in Mississippi.

33:13.208 --> 33:15.602
The gentleman I'm thinking of
is a white man.

33:15.732 --> 33:17.865
Chick Nelson.

33:17.996 --> 33:22.174
I'll reach out and see if he can
help us get your son home.

33:22.957 --> 33:24.350
Thank you, Mr. Rayner.

33:24.480 --> 33:26.265
I make no guarantees.

33:26.395 --> 33:31.139
If your Uncle Mose isn't willing
to defy the sheriff's orders,

33:31.270 --> 33:33.794
he likely has good reason.

33:33.924 --> 33:36.231
All this attention
won't make it any easier

33:36.362 --> 33:37.754
for your family down there.

33:37.885 --> 33:40.192
We just appreciate you trying.

33:42.803 --> 33:45.501
And there is a matter of cost.

33:45.632 --> 33:48.026
I don't care how much it costs.

33:50.071 --> 33:53.248
You bring my boy home.
You will get your money.

33:54.206 --> 33:56.686
MAN: Well, you know, they say
this boy was 14,

33:56.817 --> 33:58.819
but then when they showed
the body,

33:58.949 --> 34:00.821
he had a dong on him
like a horse.

34:00.951 --> 34:02.997
WOMAN: I feel for her,
but blaming the whole state

34:03.128 --> 34:04.303
isn't gonna help her case.

34:04.651 --> 34:07.871
Hoodlum trash making us all look
like a bunch of savages.

34:08.002 --> 34:09.699
I hope they fry.

34:12.789 --> 34:14.661
[sighs]

34:15.923 --> 34:18.404
Uh, coffee, please.
H-Heavy on the cream.

34:18.534 --> 34:20.841
[mid-tempo rock music playing]

34:20.971 --> 34:22.843
♪♪

34:22.973 --> 34:24.845
Down here on assignment?

34:26.412 --> 34:27.543
That obvious?

34:28.675 --> 34:30.242
Chet Packton.
I'm in from Jackson.

34:30.372 --> 34:31.895
I'm covering
for the Daily News.

34:32.026 --> 34:34.507
Ah. Dan Wakefield.
The Nation.

34:36.683 --> 34:38.859
When I stepped off
the bus from New York,

34:38.989 --> 34:40.513
I thought I'd get right to it,
so I went door to door

34:40.643 --> 34:42.167
to see if I could get
a statement.

34:42.297 --> 34:43.690
[chuckles]

34:43.820 --> 34:45.083
Let me just say,
a few people were kind enough

34:45.213 --> 34:47.302
to say, "No comment."

34:47.433 --> 34:48.564
Give yourself a few days.

34:48.999 --> 34:50.392
You'll figure out how things
work down here real quick.

34:50.523 --> 34:52.046
I take it they don't warm
to outsiders.

34:52.177 --> 34:53.569
Why do you think
you're still thirsty?

34:53.700 --> 34:56.094
[both chuckle]

34:56.224 --> 34:57.660
♪♪

34:57.791 --> 34:58.748
They're gonna have
a tough time

34:58.879 --> 35:00.489
finding an impartial jury
down here.

35:00.620 --> 35:02.361
Jury?

35:02.491 --> 35:04.102
You're getting way ahead
of yourself.

35:04.232 --> 35:06.452
There's a body.
And a confession.

35:06.582 --> 35:08.149
You don't think they'll indict?

35:09.846 --> 35:12.719
Like I said,
give yourself a few days.

35:14.677 --> 35:17.115
Can you bring us over another
cup when you can, Dottie?

35:18.159 --> 35:19.595
My friend here needs to wake up.

35:21.771 --> 35:24.948
My God. [sighs]

35:25.079 --> 35:26.863
The condition.

35:26.994 --> 35:28.691
[sighs]

35:28.822 --> 35:31.651
And if I'd have known, I--
I'd have saved you the time

35:31.781 --> 35:34.697
of loading him up,
driving all the way out here.

35:34.828 --> 35:37.178
Sir, this child's mother
had to make a helluva

35:37.309 --> 35:39.615
lot of promises
for this to happen.

35:39.746 --> 35:41.748
Don't tell us
you've changed your mind.

35:41.878 --> 35:43.837
I hate to, but I gotta.

35:43.967 --> 35:45.360
I'm sorry.

35:45.491 --> 35:47.449
Can't you keep the body
at Century Burial

35:47.580 --> 35:49.625
till you find someone else
willing to prep and ship it?

35:49.756 --> 35:51.540
Absolutely not.

35:52.411 --> 35:55.936
The law's gonna be watching us,
making sure we follow orders.

35:56.066 --> 35:59.244
Mr. Nelson,
as far as the law is concerned,

35:59.374 --> 36:02.116
that body is in the ground.

36:02.247 --> 36:05.119
You help us now,
and the story's over.

36:05.250 --> 36:07.426
This mother just wants
to see her boy again.

36:07.556 --> 36:10.994
If I prep this body
for shipment to Chicago,

36:11.125 --> 36:13.214
I need your word
you won't let her.

36:14.346 --> 36:15.521
Won't let her what?

36:15.651 --> 36:18.219
See the body.

36:18.350 --> 36:19.699
You've seen it.

36:21.179 --> 36:22.528
She shouldn't have to.

36:23.964 --> 36:25.400
That's my condition.

36:25.531 --> 36:29.361
♪♪

36:30.536 --> 36:32.973
JOHN:
Was the wheelchair necessary?

36:33.103 --> 36:35.454
GENE: We don't know
what's going to happen today.

36:35.584 --> 36:39.240
If he's not on that train,
God knows how she'll react.

36:39.371 --> 36:40.415
And if he is...

36:40.546 --> 36:42.156
[flashbulb clicks]

36:42.287 --> 36:44.202
...well, we don't know
what then, either.

36:44.332 --> 36:47.553
[bell dinging,
brakes squealing]

36:48.641 --> 36:53.080
My God, Mamie,
look at all of 'em.

36:53.211 --> 36:54.299
[flashbulbs clicking]

36:54.429 --> 36:56.083
They showed up for him.

36:58.085 --> 36:59.913
What if something goes wrong,
Daddy?

37:00.043 --> 37:01.828
What if he doesn't make it?

37:03.612 --> 37:05.179
They're here for you,
too, honey.

37:05.310 --> 37:07.225
[flashbulb clicks]

37:08.617 --> 37:10.184
Curtis. Curtis!

37:10.315 --> 37:12.186
[chuckles]

37:12.317 --> 37:13.970
Oh, Curtis!

37:14.101 --> 37:16.408
[breathing shakily]

37:16.538 --> 37:18.061
Are you okay?

37:18.192 --> 37:19.411
GENE: Just breathe.

37:22.283 --> 37:24.807
[door clanking]

37:24.938 --> 37:28.550
♪♪

37:28.681 --> 37:32.293
♪♪

37:32.424 --> 37:34.295
[flashbulbs clicking]

37:34.426 --> 37:38.821
♪♪

37:38.952 --> 37:43.261
♪♪

37:43.391 --> 37:45.611
-[crying] Emmett.
-GENE: Mamie.

37:45.741 --> 37:46.960
You didn't--
you didn't...

37:47.090 --> 37:48.831
GENE: Baby, baby,
baby, baby.

37:50.006 --> 37:52.922
No! No! Emmett!

37:54.576 --> 37:57.144
We got you. We got you,
we got you, we got you.

37:57.275 --> 37:59.102
[sobbing]

37:59.233 --> 38:03.237
♪♪

38:03.368 --> 38:07.328
♪♪

38:07.459 --> 38:09.896
You didn't die for nothing.

38:10.026 --> 38:11.724
No! My son!

38:11.854 --> 38:15.902
♪♪

38:16.032 --> 38:20.123
♪♪

38:20.254 --> 38:21.603
No!

38:21.734 --> 38:23.605
[sobbing continues]

38:23.736 --> 38:29.002
♪♪

38:29.132 --> 38:34.355
♪♪

38:34.486 --> 38:36.226
[brakes squeak]

38:36.357 --> 38:38.228
[engine shuts off]

38:57.726 --> 38:59.337
Thank you for coming,
Mr. Jackson.

39:05.168 --> 39:07.649
You're asking me to spend
the rest of my life

39:07.780 --> 39:11.349
wondering if my child
is in that box?

39:11.479 --> 39:15.135
When Mr. Nelson agreed
to prepare Emmett's body,

39:15.265 --> 39:16.832
he did so
with the understanding

39:16.963 --> 39:19.357
that the casket
would never be opened.

39:19.487 --> 39:21.271
He did this under
whose authority?

39:21.402 --> 39:22.447
His own.

39:23.448 --> 39:26.494
Mr. Nelson put himself
and everyone down there at risk

39:26.625 --> 39:28.409
when he defied sheriff's orders.

39:29.715 --> 39:32.631
Because of him,
as far as they're concerned,

39:32.761 --> 39:34.981
Emmett's buried
in your uncle's churchyard.

39:35.111 --> 39:38.071
Until now.
You saw those cameras.

39:38.201 --> 39:40.334
I won't let them cover this up.

39:40.465 --> 39:41.814
I won't do it.

39:41.944 --> 39:46.775
He sealed that casket
to protect everyone involved.

39:46.906 --> 39:48.081
Including you.

39:49.474 --> 39:51.650
I just don't think
this is something

39:51.780 --> 39:53.173
a mother could handle.

39:53.434 --> 39:56.002
I didn't think I could handle
a lot of things in my life,

39:56.132 --> 40:00.180
Mr. Rayner, but I handled them,
and I will handle this.

40:01.224 --> 40:05.403
I am not leaving
until I see my boy.

40:05.533 --> 40:07.187
[breathing heavily]

40:07.927 --> 40:09.929
[sighs]

40:16.936 --> 40:18.198
We're ready.

40:40.263 --> 40:42.135
I need to stand alone with him.

40:51.753 --> 40:57.672
♪♪

40:57.803 --> 41:03.722
♪♪

41:03.852 --> 41:09.771
♪♪

41:09.902 --> 41:15.777
♪♪

41:15.908 --> 41:21.827
♪♪

41:21.957 --> 41:27.789
♪♪

41:27.920 --> 41:30.096
MAMIE: Shh.
EMMETT: [coos]

41:30.226 --> 41:33.316
MAMIE:
You just got here, and they're
telling me I gotta give you up.

41:34.753 --> 41:37.712
Uh-oh. I know.
It's cold.

41:37.843 --> 41:44.458
♪♪

41:44.589 --> 41:51.247
♪♪

41:51.378 --> 41:57.950
♪♪

41:58.080 --> 42:04.652
♪♪

42:04.783 --> 42:07.002
-How you doing?
-EMMETT: [coos]

42:07.133 --> 42:09.048
MAMIE: [chuckles]

42:10.658 --> 42:11.920
Yes.

42:13.052 --> 42:14.314
It's good to see you.

42:14.444 --> 42:19.058
♪♪

42:19.188 --> 42:23.845
♪♪

42:23.976 --> 42:26.152
I want him to be free.

42:26.282 --> 42:32.811
♪♪

42:32.941 --> 42:39.469
♪♪

42:39.600 --> 42:46.041
♪♪

42:46.172 --> 42:52.613
♪♪

42:52.744 --> 42:59.272
♪♪

42:59.402 --> 43:05.887
♪♪

43:06.018 --> 43:12.590
♪♪

43:12.720 --> 43:19.161
♪♪

43:19.292 --> 43:25.777
♪♪

43:25.907 --> 43:32.392
♪♪

43:32.522 --> 43:34.742
MAMIE:
[breathing shakily]

43:34.873 --> 43:40.443
♪♪

43:40.574 --> 43:46.580
♪♪

43:46.711 --> 43:49.409
No one will believe it.

43:49.539 --> 43:51.063
What they did.

43:54.849 --> 43:56.372
People need to know.

43:57.939 --> 43:59.680
And you will tell them.

43:59.811 --> 44:02.161
-Of course.
-And you will show them.

44:02.291 --> 44:03.902
Take his picture.
As he is.

44:04.032 --> 44:05.251
Yes, ma'am.

44:05.381 --> 44:06.731
What are y'all waiting for?

44:06.861 --> 44:11.997
♪♪

44:12.127 --> 44:13.955
[breathing shakily]

44:14.086 --> 44:19.352
♪♪

44:19.482 --> 44:24.749
♪♪

44:33.758 --> 44:35.324
I want a public wake.

44:36.282 --> 44:38.023
Tonight.

44:38.153 --> 44:39.328
Open casket.

44:39.459 --> 44:41.896
And I don't want you doing
a thing to him.

44:43.942 --> 44:47.554
With all due respect,

44:47.685 --> 44:51.950
photos in a magazine
are one thing,

44:52.080 --> 44:54.474
but people are gonna see him.

44:55.344 --> 44:56.911
Up close.

44:59.044 --> 45:04.092
Let me fix him up
s-so he's presentable.

45:07.879 --> 45:09.010
I am not asking.

45:09.271 --> 45:11.143
♪ There's a battle
raging somewhere♪

45:11.273 --> 45:16.365
Let the people see
what they did to my boy.

45:16.496 --> 45:19.064
♪ And its thunder shakes
the ground♪

45:19.194 --> 45:21.849
♪ A terrible silence♪

45:21.980 --> 45:24.460
♪ When it's over♪

45:24.591 --> 45:28.247
♪ Only death makes
such a sound♪

45:29.509 --> 45:34.035
♪ And I see, yes, I see♪

45:34.819 --> 45:38.126
♪ On the last day of July♪
